// kaise Promise help karta hai IOC mein explanation with example
function getBalance(userId, callback) {
    setTimeout(() => {
        console.log("Fetching balance from DB...");
        let balance = 4000;  // Assume user has â‚¹4000
        callback(balance);  // ðŸ”¥ Callback function ko call kiya, balance pass kiya
    }, 2000);
}

// âœ… Yahan pe hum ek function pass kar rahe hain `callback` ke jagah
getBalance(123, function (balance) { 
    if (balance > 5000) {
        console.log("âœ… Transaction Allowed");
    } else {
        console.log("âŒ Transaction Denied: Low Balance");
    }
});

â€¢	getBalance() ke paas pura control hai!
â€¢	Agar getBalance() callback call na kare, ya kisi galti se galat balance bhej de, toh transaction fail ho sakta hai!
â€¢	Humare haath me kuch nahi hai, jo function karega woh hoga.
â€¢	Koi error handling bhi nahi hai agar database error de de.


Solution: Promises Fix IoC Problem
Ab hum Promises use karenge taaki execution control wapas le sakein! ðŸš€
--
function getBalance(userId) {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
        setTimeout(() => {
            console.log("Fetching balance from DB...");
            let balance = 4000; // Assume user has â‚¹4000
            
            if (balance !== undefined) {
                resolve(balance); // âœ… Control return to caller
            } else {
                reject("âŒ Database Error: Balance not found");
            }
        }, 2000);
    });
}

// âœ… Caller now has full control!
getBalance(123)
    .then((balance) => {
        if (balance > 5000) {
            console.log("âœ… Transaction Allowed");
        } else {
            console.log("âŒ Transaction Denied: Low Balance");
        }
    })
    .catch((error) => {
        console.log("Error:", error); // Error handle kar sakte hain!
    });

How Promises Solve IoC?
---
Problem with Callbacks
-----------------------
getBalance() callback ke control mein tha
Agar callback call na ho, toh kuch nahi kar sakte
Koi proper error handling nahi

Solution with Promises
-----------------------
getBalance() sirf resolve() ya reject() karega, but control .then() ke paas hoga!
.then() caller ke haath me hai, woh decide karega ki kya karna hai!
catch() se error ko properly handle kar sakte hain!


IoC ka problem yeh hai ki hum execution control kisi aur ke haath de dete hain.
âœ” Promises se hum execution ka control wapas le aate hain!
âœ” Ab .then() aur .catch() se hum decide kar sakte hain ki kab kya execute hoga.
âœ” Jo kaam pehle callback kar raha tha, woh ab resolve() aur reject() kar raha hai, par control user ke paas hai!

